To find the distance between \(P=(1,4)\) and \(Q=(11,9)\), use the distance formula  
 \(d = \sqrt{(x_2-x_1)^2 + (y_2-y_1)^2}\).  

Here  
 \(\Delta x = 11 - 1 = 10\),  
 \(\Delta y = 9 - 4 = 5\).  

So  
 \(d = \sqrt{10^2 + 5^2}  
       = \sqrt{100 + 25}  
       = \sqrt{125}  
       = 5\sqrt{5}  
       \approx 11.18\).
